reviews.text: I‚Äôd come back for the bathroom alone haha, but the food is absolutely amazing.  My wife lived in Brazil and really loved it.  She has been 3 times in 2 weeks now.  They also have a little play place for kids with a bunch of toys.  Really cool atmosphere that complements the food perfectly.  I got the Floripa Flex and really liked it.  My wife‚Äôs favorite is the Samba.

Great service, and the servers fill your bowl to the top with whatever you want! The a√ßa√≠ is fresh and delicious as was the pi√±a colada base. Great toppings and fruits and generous portions! Will definitely be back!

The bowls are amazing! I built my own using the pb/acai/protein base and it's delicious. My wife tried the Rio and loved it too. It's super cute inside with tons of plants and great lighting and decor. They don't charge extra for getting whatever toppings you want. And the cheese bread is so great too. Today was our first visit and we'll be back soon!!

My bestie has been to places like this before and wanted to take me, so we finally went today! It was such a cool spot. The employee who helped us was incredibly friendly and let me sample a few flavors since it was my first time. I ended up getting the peanut butter bowl, and it was amazing, great flavor and an awesome amount of protein for the prize!

Rio Acai is my favorite spot for Brazilian acai bowls. There is so much variety in the bases and toppings. It's easy to reorder your favorite or try something completely new.

I have two kids with severe allergies, and Rio Acai has always been incredibly accommodating. I was at the grand opening for this location and they happily got out new scoops and cleaned work stations to ensure a safe experience for my children.

The coconut base is my favorite. It's sweet and goes really well with all of the fruit, toppings and drizzles. For a dash of protein, I really enjoy the peanut butter crumble.
